<module>
    <h>gu</h>
    <p><g>gu</g>
        <en>-ly</en> is the adverbialising particle, which creates <a
            href="?xx=prepositions/adverbs">adverb</a>-like expressions of manner out of <a
            href="?xx=adjectives/adjectives">adjectives</a>.</p>

    <section>
        <h>dependents</h>
        <section id="deps-comp">
            <h>complement</h>
            <p><g>gu</g> takes an <a href="?xx=adjectives/adjectives">adjective</a> as its
                complement, deriving an adverbial of manner.</p>
            <p>Some examples – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Tha Calum sgìth – tha e ag obair <m>gu trang</m> anns an achadh.</gd>
                        <tr>Malcolm is tired – he is working busily in the field.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 7</ref>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Ciamar a tha sibh? Tha mi <m>gu math</m>, tapadh leibh.</gd>
                        <tr>How are you? I am well, thank you.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 15</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl>
            </p>
            <p>cf. <a href="?gd=dearbh"><g>gu dearbh</g></a>
                <en>indeed, certainly</en></p>
        </section>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h>uses</h>
        <section id="uses-mod">
            <h>modifier</h>
            <p>Some examples as modifier of a verbal noun – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Tha Calum sgìth – tha e ag obair <m>gu trang</m> anns an achadh.</gd>
                        <tr>Malcolm is tired – he is working busily in the field.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 7</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl>
            </p>
            <p>cf. <a href="?gd=dearbh"><g>gu dearbh</g></a>
                <en>indeed, certainly</en> as root modifier</p>
        </section>
        <section id="uses-pred">
            <h>predicate</h>
            <p>Some examples as predicate of <a href="?gd=bi"><g>bi</g></a>
                <en>be</en> – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Ciamar a tha sibh? Tha mi <m>gu math</m>, tapadh leibh.</gd>
                        <tr>How are you? I am well, thank you.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 15</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl>
            </p>

        </section>

    </section>

</module>
